<OrgName><entry>TB SPECIALIST NURSE SERVICE</entry>
</OrgName>
<Desc><entry>NHS service aiming to minimise the impact of TB on individuals and the community at large.  Follows up suspected and existing TB cases and provides a home based contact tracing and screening service.  Provides training and advice on TB to relevant professionals and the general public.  Also provides BCG advice.  A BCG vaccination clinic is held at the Central Health Clinic for people needing vaccination who fulfil services criteria.</entry>
</Desc>
